commit.message:
Remote mode stream destinations changed.
I had to reconcile original flac123 behavior with legacy mpg321 behavior,
and I settled on stdout for non-error messages and stderr for errors.

--buffer-time option replaces --buffer-size passed to libao driver.
You may need to specify a smaller value (like 500) in remote mode to get
smooth scrolling with 24-bit files.

bad popt options now detected
Cygwin default libao driver in configure.ac (#1)

update README.md to make copy and paste easier
AM_INIT_AUTOMAKE([foreign]) to relax README requirement
8-bit depth fix with proper wav output on macOS

Revert "8-bit depth fix"
This reverts commit 515f635828a8f0265c2b9543313de8e045061342.
